    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Peconic was once called Hermitage before the name Peconic was adopted in the 19th century.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peconic%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In the late 1800s, Peconic hosted the Peconic School, an artist colony led by painters like Benjamin Fitz and Edith Prellwitz.",
